BaseCacheDao is an example of how DAO provides a pluggable framework.
In practice, caching can be done declaratively through SQL Maps, making this somewhat redundant.
Channels are applied per class....so if you only have one cache DAO, then you only have one channel.
When getting or putting an item in a channel, synchronization is applied on CHANNELS.
A CacheChannel holds a cache and a list of keys.
If a channel for the class is not found in CHANNELS, a new one is created.
CacheChannel contains a HashMap named cache to store data.
CacheChannel maintains a List named keys to store identifiers of cached items.
